<TITLE> Alleged extremist killed in 'gunfight' with RAB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Apr 07 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected extremist was killed in a gunfight with RAB in Kushtia on Wednesday, police said. Police claimed that the deceased, Ashraful Islam alias Mandar, 40, was the commander of a banned extremist outfit JSD Ganabahini. Ashraful, son of Alfaj Mondol, hailed from Khordbakhil village of Kushtia Sadar upazila. CA Halim, assistant police superintendent of Kushtia, said RAB-12 members, tipped by sources, went on an operation at Bakhil Maddhyapara playground at 7pm, where some armed extremists were having a secret meeting. Suspecting the presence of RAB, they set off bombs and opened fire. Halim said there was an exchange of fire for about twenty minutes. The body of Mandar was found after his companions escaped. Police recovered a 0.22 bore rifle, a light gun, four cocktails, 12 rounds of bullets and a large machete. Ashraf has seven cases against him, including four murder cases. bd
